The paper proposes a new framework for lifelong learning that incorporates neural architecture search. Therefore, it is likely to belong to the sub-category of machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The experiments involve image datasets, indicating a possible connection to computer vision (cs.CV). The use of neural architecture search suggests a connection to neural networks (cs.NE). Finally, the paper involves natural language processing tasks, indicating a possible connection to computational linguistics (cs.CL).
